messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /api/paste/{paste_id}

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has @RequestMapping("/api/paste") at class level, and the method has @DeleteMapping(path = "/{paste_id}"), so the combined route is /api/paste/{paste_id}.
- The code explicitly defines @DeleteMapping(path = "/{paste_id}") on deleteCodePasteWithId, so DELETE is supported for that path.
- The same controller also has @GetMapping(path = "/{paste_id}") (getCodePasteFromId), so GET is explicitly supported for the same path.
- No annotation in the source explicitly maps HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, PATCH or POST to the path /api/paste/{paste_id}; therefore, based strictly on the code (not on framework behavior or assumptions), those methods are not acceptable for this endpoint.
- "All methods" is false because the controller maps specific methods (GET and DELETE) rather than permitting every HTTP method.
